The paper deals with optimization of interference management in device-to-device (D2D) communications, which is a key issue in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power control and beamforming, which are topics related to signal processing (cs.SI). The paper introduces a novel optimization method called matrix fractional programming (FP), which is a mathematical optimization technique and falls under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for coordinating scheduling in D2D networks, which is related to system design and control (cs.SY).
